http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Mangalore/Ramanath-Rai-inaugurates-sports-meet/article13989308.ece

Minister for Environment and Forest B. Ramanath Rai on Friday inaugurated the third annual sports meet of Karnataka State Pollution Control Board at the NITK grounds in Surathkal. He said the meet would enhance mental and physical strength of the PCB, who were striving for preserving environment and containing pollution. B.A. Mohiuddin Bava, Mangaluru North MLA, said that many sports events were being held at Mangaluru and in Dakshina Kannada, which was a welcome sign. KSPCB chairman Lakshman and others were present. About 700 employees of the PCB from across the State are participating in the meet.